cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "CFOBenchmark: an honest evaluation suite for financial LLMs"
message: "If you use this software, please cite it."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Takhirov
    given-names: Erbol
repository-code: "https://github.com/ErbolTakhirov/CFOBenchmark"
license: MIT
version: 0.1.0-rc1
date-released: "2026-07-11"
abstract: >
  An evaluation suite for financial language models that reports what it measured and refuses to
  report what it did not. It wraps FinQA, TAT-QA, FinanceReasoning, FinanceBench, ConvFinQA and
  SECQUE, adds a deterministic small-business CFO benchmark whose gold answers come from Python
  oracles rather than an LLM, and evaluates retrieval, conversation, tool use, and refusal under
  adversarial pressure. Official metrics are parity-tested against the real upstream evaluators.
  Scores that cannot be trusted are withheld rather than published with a caveat.
keywords:
  - financial-nlp
  - llm-evaluation
  - benchmark
  - retrieval-augmented-generation
  - hallucination-detection
